        text: 'auto',
      },
    ],
    comment: '<p>The HTML input form <code>autofocus</code> attribute is used to specify an <code>&#x3C;input></code> element to have focus once the web page is loaded.</p>\n<p>Example:</p>\n<pre><code class="language-html">&#x3C;form action="/credit_card.php">\n  Full name: &#x3C;input type="text"\n    name="fullname" autofocus>\n  Card number: &#x3C;input type="number"\n    name="ccnumber">\n  Exparation date: &#x3C;input type="month"\n    name="ccdate">\n  CV: &#x3C;input type"number"\n    name="cvnumber">\n  &#x3C;input type="submit">\n&#x3C;/form>  \n</code></pre>\n<p><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" width="320" height="51"><defs><path id="b" d="M101 16h131v19H101z"/><filter id="a" width="109.2%" height="163.2%" x="-4.6%" y="-31.6%" filterUnits="objectBoundingBox"><feOffset in="SourceAlpha" result="shadowOffsetOuter1"/><feGaussianBlur in="shadowOffsetOuter1" result="shadowBlurOuter1" stdDeviation="2"/><feComposite in="shadowBlurOuter1" in2="SourceAlpha" operator="out" result="shadowBlurOuter1"/><feColorMatrix in="shadowBlurOuter1" values="0 0 0 0 0.439215686 0 0 0 0 0.662745098 0 0 0 0 0.905882353 0 0 0 1 0"/></filter></defs><g fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd"><rect width="320" height="51" fill="#FFF" rx="9"/><use fill="#000" filter="url(#a)" xlink:href="#b"/><path fill="#FFF" stroke="#70A9E7" stroke-linejoin="square" d="M101.5 16.5h130v18h-130z"/><text fill="#000" font-family="ArialMT, Arial" font-size="16"><tspan x="20" y="31">Full Name:</tspan></text></g></svg></p>\n<!--[View CodePen](https://codepen.io/enkidevs/pen/djbrLP)--> \n<p>In the example above, the first text field has the autofocus set, so when the page loads, the text box will be selected by default and the user can start entering text right away without having to click the textfield.  </p>\n<p>You can assign <code>autofocus</code> as either <code>autofocus</code>, <code>autofocus=""</code> or <code>autofocus="autofocus"</code>. All three options work the same in HTML5 however,  if you\'re using XHTML <code>autofocus</code> is required to be written as <code>autofocus="autofocus"</code>.</p>\n',
  },
